  {
    "node_id": "0061",
    "title": "可持续的增长路径",
    "page_range": "42",
    "summary": "This section addresses the limitations of current marketing growth strategies and introduces the need for a sustainable growth framework. It can answer questions regarding:\n- **Topics:** Sustainable growth paths, the shift from short-term conversion optimization to long-term user connection building, and the ceiling of \"performance-first\" marketing.\n- **Entities:** Aarki (data source), marketers, end users.\n- **Metrics (Year-over-Year):** User acquisition (UA) costs increased by 12%; overall advertising budgets grew by 26%; user scale growth stagnated at 2%.\n- **Claims:** The widening gap between marketing investment and user growth indicates that performance-driven strategies have reached their limit. Marketers urgently need a new framework prioritizing authentic user connections over short-term conversions.\n- **Evidence Types:** Quantitative industry data and trend metrics sourced from Aarki (referenced via footnotes).\n- **Dates/Timeframes:** Year-over-year (同比) comparisons; no specific calendar year is provided.\n- **Definitions/Procedures/Tables/Figures:** None present in this section."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0062",
    "title": "移动增长，本质上就是全链路增长",
    "page_range": "42",
    "summary": "This section addresses the following retrieval focus areas:\n- **Topics & Claims:** Establishes that \"mobile growth\" (移动增长) is fundamentally equivalent to \"full-link growth\" (全链路增长).\n- **Definitions:** Provides a conceptual definition equating mobile growth with a full-link operational approach.\n- **Answerable Questions:** What is the essential nature of mobile growth? How is mobile growth conceptually defined in relation to full-link strategies?\n- **Missing Data Types:** Contains no specific entities, dates, procedures, metrics, tables, figures, or evidence types. It functions strictly as a high-level declarative statement."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0063",
    "title": "关键变化",
    "page_range": "42-43",
    "summary": "This section addresses mobile app growth challenges and strategic marketing shifts. It can answer retrieval questions regarding:\n• **Metrics & Churn Data:** What is the current mobile game user churn rate? (>95% of iOS and Google Play mobile game installs churn within 30 days, per Business of Apps 2025 data).\n• **Key Dates & Projections:** When is the critical turning point for sustainable app growth projected to occur? (2026).\n• **Definitions & Strategic Frameworks:** What defines true sustainable growth in mobile marketing? (A retention-driven, full-funnel collaborative mechanism where user acquisition, engagement, and remarketing operate as a unified learning system rather than isolated channels).\n• **Claims & Industry Trends:** How are performance and brand metrics evolving? (Retention is becoming the new performance metric, and performance marketing is becoming the new brand, as stated by Rajeev Ranjan, VP of Product at Aarki).\n• **Entities & Evidence Types:** Which organizations and data sources support these insights? (Business of Apps, Aarki, Statista; evidence includes 2025 industry reports, global mobile user forecasts, churn rate datasets, and executive commentary).\nThe section contains no tables or figures but provides specific quantitative metrics, strategic definitions, and cited industry reports for factual retrieval."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0064",
    "title": "传统投放链路在「用户安装」时结束，而真正的增长机会恰恰从这里开始。",
    "page_range": "43",
    "summary": "This section addresses the endpoint of traditional advertising funnels and the starting point of post-installation growth. It supports retrieval for:\n- **Topics & Entities:** 投放链路 (advertising/delivery chain), 用户安装 (user installation), 增长机会 (growth opportunities).\n- **Claims:** Traditional acquisition chains conventionally terminate at user installation; meaningful growth opportunities begin immediately after installation.\n- **Definitions/Concepts:** Delineates the strategic boundary between traditional acquisition (ending at install) and modern growth strategies (starting post-install).\n- **Answerable Questions:** Where does the traditional advertising funnel end? When do real user growth opportunities begin? What marks the transition from acquisition to retention/growth phases?\n- **Procedures, Dates, Tables, Figures, Metrics, Evidence Types:** None provided in this section."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0065",
    "title": "增长并非单向链路，而是持续循环",
    "page_range": "43",
    "summary": "This section addresses questions regarding the conceptual nature of modern growth strategies. It provides a foundational definition and claim that contemporary growth is not a linear, one-way process, but rather a continuous, self-reinforcing cycle. Specifically, it characterizes growth as an ongoing exchange that accumulates over time among three core components/entities: signals, content, and behavior. The content is attributed to Aarki (www.aarki.com). It does not contain specific dates, operational procedures, quantitative metrics, tables, figures, or empirical evidence types."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0066",
    "title": "左侧循环：用户获取（UA）",
    "page_range": "43",
    "summary": "This section defines the \"Left Loop: User Acquisition (UA)\" entity. It answers questions regarding the core definition and primary function of UA, specifically stating that its role is to capture user attention and convert it into initial user actions. The section does not contain dates, procedural steps, quantitative metrics, tables, figures, or evidentiary support."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0067",
    "title": "右侧循环：再营销（RT）",
    "page_range": "43",
    "summary": "This section defines the \"Right Loop: Remarketing (RT)\" concept and its operational purpose. It supports retrieval for questions regarding:\n- **Topic & Definition:** What is the \"Right Loop: Remarketing (RT)\"?\n- **Procedure/Mechanism:** How is the remarketing process executed? (Through continuous interaction with users)\n- **Claims & Goals:** What are the primary objectives of this loop? (To re-activate users and continuously strengthen retention)\n- **Entities:** Users.\nThe section does not contain specific dates, quantitative metrics, tables, figures, or cited evidence types."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0068",
    "title": "核心引擎：Aarki 的差异化能力",
    "page_range": "43-44",
    "summary": "This section addresses retrieval queries regarding Aarki’s core technological architecture and growth methodology. It covers:\n• **Topics & Entities:** Aarki’s core engine, Supervised AI, Creative Intelligence, Data Feedback Loop, and the “Infinity Loop” model.\n• **Definitions:** Defines the core engine as a system driven by Supervised AI, Creative Intelligence, and a closed-loop data feedback mechanism. Defines Supervised AI as a hybrid of human contextual insight and machine precision that learns in real-time from campaign performance. Defines the Infinity Loop as a cyclical, interconnected growth framework that replaces linear funnels.\n• **Procedures & Mechanisms:** Details the operational workflow: real-time performance learning → cross-channel insight application → transparent and controllable optimization during data signal decay → retention-stage insights continuously reshaping acquisition strategies → user engagement progression (cognition → recognition/alignment → active sharing).\n• **Claims:** Asserts that this architecture elevates automation from a simple efficiency tool to a sustainable competitive advantage, and that each growth cycle inherently reinforces the next.\n• **Tables, Figures, Metrics, Dates & Evidence Types:** Contains no specific dates, quantitative metrics, empirical evidence, or explicit table/figure references. Mentions a conceptual visual structure (central engine with left/right growth cycles and the Infinity Loop model) but provides no data-backed evidence or citations.\n• **Retrieval Utility:** Optimized for questions on Aarki’s AI optimization methodology, its strategy for handling data signal decay, the mechanics of its cyclical growth model, and its strategic positioning of marketing automation."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0069",
    "title": "全链路增长框架——新一代移动增长的标准范式",
    "page_range": "44",
    "summary": "This section can answer questions regarding:\n- **Topics & Entities:** Aarki’s “Full-Link Growth Framework” (全链路增长框架) and its positioning as a new standard paradigm for mobile growth.\n- **Definition:** What the framework is—a unified, continuously operating system that integrates User Acquisition (UA), Retargeting (RT), and User Lifecycle Management into a single growth engine to achieve scalable and profitable growth.\n- **Procedures/Mechanisms:** How the system operates iteratively: data signals are converted into decisions, creative deployments are accumulated as intelligent assets, and each campaign cycle reinforces subsequent growth rounds.\n- **Claims:** That the framework is a simple, replicable growth system evolved from Aarki’s “infinite loop” concept.\n- **Dates, Metrics, Tables, Figures, Evidence Types:** Not addressed in this section."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0070",
    "title": "当前现状：",
    "page_range": "44",
    "summary": "This section addresses the current evolution of business growth strategies, specifically answering questions about the transition from a \"growth cycle\" to a \"value cycle.\" It covers:\n• **Topics & Claims:** The strategic shift from pure growth to value optimization; the claim that every creative choice, feedback signal, and user behavior generates actionable insights for improving User Lifetime Value (LTV).\n• **Entities & Metrics:** Core metric: LTV (用户生命周期价值). Key input entities: creative choices, signal feedback, user behavior.\n• **Definitions & Concepts:** Implicitly defines the \"value cycle\" as a continuous, insight-driven feedback loop where user interactions and creative decisions directly inform LTV enhancement.\n• **Procedures, Tables, Figures, Evidence Types, Dates:** None provided in this section.\n• **Retrieval-Ready Questions:** What is the current trend in growth strategy? How do user behaviors and creative choices impact LTV? What constitutes a value cycle? What data sources drive user value optimization?"
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0071",
    "title": "应用商店已不再是唯一的增长入口。",
    "page_range": "44",
    "summary": "This section addresses the shift in digital product growth strategies, claiming that app stores are no longer the exclusive user acquisition channel. It identifies the specific entities and touchpoints now driving ecosystem access: Web, mobile platforms, Webshops, and third-party app stores. The content can answer retrieval queries regarding: (1) current growth entry points and channel diversification; (2) how user access behavior has evolved toward multi-platform ecosystem entry; and (3) which emerging touchpoints supplement or replace traditional app stores. No dates, formal definitions, step-by-step procedures, tables, figures, quantitative metrics, or cited evidence types are present in this section."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0072",
    "title": "分发渠道不断多元化。",
    "page_range": "44",
    "summary": "This section can answer questions related to:\n- **Topics:** Trends in distribution channel development and strategic competitive positioning.\n- **Claims:** Distribution channels are continuously diversifying; the ability to design and coordinate \"proprietary user experience\" (自有用户体验) will become the most critical competitive advantage.\n- **Definitions/Concepts:** \"Proprietary user experience\" framed as a strategic capability encompassing both design and coordination.\n- **Entities, Dates, Procedures, Tables, Figures, Metrics, Evidence Types:** None present. The section contains only high-level strategic assertions without specific organizations, timelines, operational steps, visual aids, quantitative data, or cited evidence."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0073",
    "title": "机遇所在：",
    "page_range": "44-45",
    "summary": "This section addresses strategic opportunities for developers, answering questions regarding: **Topics/Claims**: What new control and responsibilities do developers have over user relationships? How will user experience friction change? How are user acquisition and remarketing strategies connected? What is the primary driver of growth? **Entities**: Developers, user relationships, user acquisition, remarketing, growth. **Metrics**: User Lifetime Value (LTV) is identified as the core growth metric. **Dates/Definitions/Procedures/Tables/Figures/Evidence**: None are provided in this excerpt. The content is conceptual and forward-looking, optimized for retrieval queries on developer strategy, marketing integration, and LTV-focused growth models."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0074",
    "title": "五条规则，一个目标：让用户留下来、提升付费率、持续提升全链路增长。用户留存的「黄金五法则」",
    "page_range": "45",
    "summary": "**Topics**: User retention strategy, onboarding design, user lifecycle management, growth strategy evaluation, ROI optimization, relationship depth vs. reach breadth, creative fatigue mitigation, content update scheduling, ad performance optimization, remarketing as R&D, marketing strategy optimization, budget allocation, and long-term value vs. short-term wins.\n**Entities**: Retention, Day 0/Day 30, onboarding flow, first payment, creative system, ROI, user loyalty, growth loop, marketing funnel, user base, Aarki (Creative Intelligence platform & company), CTR, Avi Das (Aarki CRO).\n**Dates/Timing**: Retention calculation baseline: Day 0 (immediate user contact) vs. Day 30; creative relevance decay timeframe: within days, with performance degradation after 4 ad impressions; data source timestamp: January 2025 (202501).\n**Definitions**: Retention is defined as a continuous effect system and a core indicator of overall growth strategy effectiveness, not an isolated marketing stage. \"Relationship depth\" is a quality-driven, multi-dimensional engagement model. Remarketing is fundamentally characterized as R&D, where each campaign functions as a controlled test. \"Plateau actions\" refer to strategies with stagnant performance that should be paused.\n**Procedures**: Embed engagement mechanisms into onboarding; communicate core value before first payment; align lifecycle management with creative systems; proactively plan content update rhythms and refresh creatives before attention declines; maintain consistent storytelling across growth cycles; identify value propositions for at-risk/churning users and reverse-apply insights to acquisition workflows; scale proven strategies, pause plateauing actions, and allocate budget toward long-value user groups and creative systems rather..."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0080",
    "title": "打通数据、创意与反馈，构建持续运转效果循环协同运作：用户获取、再营销与用户生命周期管理",
    "page_range": "46-47",
    "summary": "This section (Pages 46–47) analyzes the strategic integration of data, creatives, and feedback loops to optimize User Acquisition (UA), remarketing, and user lifecycle management. **Topics & Claims** contrast the inefficiencies of siloed marketing operations—which trigger audience overlap, bidding self-competition, inflated CPMs, creative exhaustion, and compounded budget waste—with the necessity of unified UA and Retention (RT) collaboration. The section claims that integrating UA-RT workflows addresses systemic pressures including rising global CPI, low user monetization (<5% overall, <2% for casual apps), extended break-even cycles (>90 days), and signal loss from tightening privacy regulations and Apple’s ATT framework. It advocates redesigning cross-functional collaboration over increasing ad spend to mitigate tracking visibility loss. **Entities** include Aarki, Darwin, Adjust, Apple App Tracking Transparency (ATT), casual apps, and Avi Das (Aarki CRO). **Dates** referenced are 2023 and 2025. **Metrics** covered include CPM, conversion rates, ~35% global ATT opt-in rate, monetization percentages, and break-even timelines. **Evidence Types** comprise industry surveys (Darwin, 2023), internal company data (Aarki, 2025), third-party benchmarks (Adjust, 2025), statistical market data, and expert industry quotes. **Tables/Figures** are not referenced. **Definitions** implicitly address bidding self-competition and creative effectiveness exhaustion. **Procedures/Context** outline audience segmentation, ad bidding dynamics, creative testing, and UA-RT workflow redesign. Optimized for retrieval on app marketing economics, privacy-driven ad-tech constraints, lifecycle management strategies, and performance loop optimization."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0087",
    "title": "可持续的全链路增长，并不意味着一味加码。掌控投放节奏，做出理性决策",
    "page_range": "48",
    "summary": "This section (page 48) introduces a strategic framework for managing ad placement pacing to achieve sustainable full-link growth without blind investment increases. It structurally organizes three core operational modes: 扩量 (Scale), 暂停 (Pause), and 再投入 (Reinvest). The content functions exclusively as a categorical index or structural heading. It does not contain definitions, procedures, dates, metrics, tables, figures, claims, or evidence types. For retrieval purposes, this node should be treated as a structural marker to locate subsequent or surrounding discussions on these three operational strategies, rather than as a source of substantive factual, procedural, or analytical data."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0091",
    "title": "只有具备可持续性的增长，才能在未来真正建立竞争优势。打造可持续的竞争优势",
    "page_range": "49",
    "summary": "This section outlines how sustainable, AI-driven marketing growth establishes long-term competitive advantage, positioning every user interaction as a catalyst for subsequent expansion. It covers topics including continuous learning systems, predictive behavioral analytics, and full-funnel growth orchestration. Key entities referenced are Aarki and its CEO, Aman Sareen, with a strategic date target of 2026 for the essential adoption of retention-centric growth frameworks. Core definitions introduce the \"unified learning engine,\" a system that integrates acquisition, engagement, and remarketing to convert behavioral patterns into predictive intelligence, and the \"full-funnel growth framework,\" a systematic approach centered on continuous learning and user retention. Primary claims assert that competitive advantage is determined by the speed of converting insights into action, with continuous learning and iterative execution serving as the foundational mechanisms of modern growth. Detailed procedures describe orchestrating acquisition, engagement, and retargeting into continuous feedback loops, leveraging AI to transform real-time user behavior into calibrated predictive models, and iteratively optimizing campaigns based on accumulated interaction data. Evidence is presented through strategic executive assertions emphasizing that iterative cycles generate cognitive insights and execution speed drives market differentiation. No tables, figures, or specific metrics are present in this section."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0093",
    "title": "Aarki 帮助打破增长天花板，持续超额达成 D90 ROI 目标成功案例",
    "page_range": "50-51",
    "summary": "This section provides retrieval-ready information to answer questions regarding:\n- **Topics:** Mobile app user reactivation, AI-driven remarketing, long-term ROI/LTV optimization, performance marketing case studies.\n- **Entities:** Aarki (solution provider), Rovio (client), Angry Birds 2 (target application), Aarki Creative Studio (creative optimization tool), Rovio User Acquisition Lead (quoted stakeholder).\n- **Timeframes & Dates:** D3, D7, D90, D365 (standard performance measurement windows); 3-month period for achieving long-term LTV targets.\n- **Definitions/Concepts:** D90/D7 ROI, D365 LTV, supervised AI remarketing system, high-value LTV user segmentation, predictive LTV modeling, dynamic bid optimization.\n- **Procedures/Methods:** Conducting in-app behavior analysis for user segmentation; deploying predictive models to estimate LTV and dynamically adjust bids; utilizing Aarki Creative Studio for data-driven creative production; applying AI targeting and iterative creative optimization.\n- **Claims/Results:** Successful reactivation of high-value churned users; consistent overachievement of ROI targets; rapid attainment of long-term LTV goals; efficient budget scaling alongside user reactivation; sustained overall campaign performance improvement.\n- **Metrics:** D90 ROI exceeded target by an average of 1.7x; D7 ROI consistently achieved ~1.3x of target; D365 LTV target met within 3 months.\n- **Evidence Types:** Quantitative performance metrics, direct client testimonial/quote, documented case study outcomes. (No specific tables or figures are detailed in the provided text.)"
  }
]
